mongodb.com --> community edition --> click community server --> Click Download.
Click next next custom --> location --> E drive --> Finish
Open command prompt --> Type 'mongod' --> this starts mongodb service in our system after which we can start working with mongodb.
Start --> type 'env' --> Click edit environment varaibles for your account. --> Double click path option.
Click New --> Click Browse --> Go to custom path we have set for mongodb installation --> click path finally bin folder and click ok.
Go to E deive--> Program files --> Mongo DB --> Server --> 6.0 --> data --> create a folder 'db' --> copy the path of this folder.
In cmd propmt type mongod --dbpath="E:\.....\db"  and press enter. 
